new_version_errors.5.19.0:
The recipe did not change in the version migration, a URL did not hash, or there is jinja2 syntax the bot cannot handle!

Please check the URLs in your recipe with version '5.19.0' to make sure they exist!

We also found the following errors:

 - could not hash URL template 'https://github.com/sbmlteam/python-libsbml/releases/download/v{{ version }}/{{ name }}.tar.gz'

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "python-libsbml" %}
{% set version = "5.19.7" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/sbmlteam/python-libsbml/releases/download/v{{ version }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 447b1fde7aceccd11a93dc9f589ffd9319ba854d7b7583f911259a8b0127ab7b

build:
  number: 1
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
    - make            # [unix]
    - cmake

  host:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - pip
    - swig >=3.0.12

  run:
    - python

test:
  # Python imports
  imports:
    - libsbml

about:
  home: http://sbml.org
  license: LGPL-2.1-only
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  license_family: LGPL
  summary: "LibSBML is an application programming interface library for reading, writing, manipulating and validating content expressed in the Systems Biology Markup Language (SBML) format. It is written in ISO C and C++, provides language bindings for Common Lisp, Java, Python, Perl, MATLAB and Octave, and includes many features that facilitate adoption and use of both SBML and the library. Developers can embed libSBML in their applications, saving themselves the work of implementing their own SBML parsing, manipulation and validation software."

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - fbergmann
